{"word":"ἐξικνέομαι","slug":"ἐξικνέομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξικνέομαι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ίξομαι</el>) (aor2 <el>-ικόμην</el>) </el><p/><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to reach, arrive at</i> a place, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to come to</i> as a suppliant, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to arrive at</i> or <i>reach</i> an object, <i>to complete, accomplish</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; so <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to reach</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—of mental operations, <el>ὅσον δυνατός εἰμι ἐξικέσθαι</el> so far as <i>I can get by inquiry</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li1000'><b>b. </b>of things, <i>to be sufficient</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}